include patterns (Test*, *Test, *Tests, *TestCase),\nso they were never scanned by the integration-test profile and have not run\nsince they were committed. They extend AbstractDataIntegrityIntegrationTest\nlike their ~82 siblings; only the file/class name differed.\n\nRename all seven to end in Test so surefire picks them up:\n\n  DataIntegrityProgramStagesNoPrograms\n  DataIntegrityOptionGroupsWithoutOptions\n  DataIntegrityUsersCaptureOrgUnitNotInTeiSearchHierarchy\n  DataIntegrityUserRolesNoUsers\n  DataIntegrityUsersCaptureOrgunitNotInDataView\n  DataIntegrityProgramInconsistentlyLinkedTrackedEntityType\n  DataIntegrityUserRolesNoAuthorities\n\nEnabling them surfaced that DataIntegrityProgramInconsistentlyLinkedTracked\nEntityType built Program instances without the enrollmentCategoryCombo that\nbecame a not-null property in #22698 (added after this test was written but\nnever run, so it never failed). Build its Programs via the createProgram /\ncreateProgramWithoutRegistration TestBase helpers, which #22698 updated to set\nboth the category combo and enrollment category combo to the default - the\nsame pattern #22698 applied to the other DataIntegrity tests. The check under\ntest (programs_inconsistent_tracked_entity_type) is unchanged and orthogonal\nto category combos; the assertions on program type / tracked entity type are\nuntouched.\n\nVerified locally: mvn -Pintegration-test -Dtest=\u003c7 classes\u003e -\u003e 12 tests, 0\nfailures, 0 errors; spotless:check passes.\n\nCaught by @david-mackessy in review of #24010.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","author":{"name":"Stian Sandvold","email":"stian@dhis2.org"},"id":"fa88269ad22128412dfa7dd70ee72e6dd9c37f3c","tree_id":"0d3b293ca7bdfeee1ebca823a9eb4a1d503b0e5a","timestamp":"2026-05-28T20:11:41Z","committer":{"name":"Stian Sandvold","email":"stian@dhis2.org"}},"workflow_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/workflows/10954","repository":{